originalText.text: The attendants are rude. I went there to park my car and ask about the price change I was told the price never changed, but I knew it did. Because I was being charged  $12 more than my previous times parking at the lot. It went from 48 for overnight to 60. I spin around the block to see if there was any place cheaper ,didn't fine a price so I went back , the attendant seen me come back in in park at the stop sign. my I got out my car and went to exit the lot. The Attending is going to tell me is $68., I said to him how was it $68 when you just told me it was 60 10 minutes ago, this 2 tone Bloch face man gone tell me the price just went up . I said so in 10 minutes the price went up eight dollars. Because I asked him that, he's gonna tell me you know what we don't have no spots available. they refused to take debit payment always want you to bring cash on top of that management never answer the phone.. just horrible all around

originalText.text:
I paid close to $700 dollars to park my car here, the first day I came to drop off the check after arranging this with their office, the lot attendant was extremely rude and refused to help me.

I had my wife drop off the check the following day; I arrive at the lot ready to drop my car off after work. This same lot attendant sitting there greets me in the same fashion as the day prior, him sucking his teeth at me and being entirely unreceptive to any questions I have all while trying to shut the door in my face.

I asked him to not give me a hard time, that I had questions, he ignores me and as he’s going to shut the door in my face again, Tells me to pull my car over and hand him the key.

I park my car, as he’s walking up, I’m explaining to him, It was explained to me that I’d be assigned a parking spot and to park my car myself, him not listening,  repeatedly demands I give him my key.

I refuse, because that was not explained to me, he continued to be dismissive and explain absolutely nothing, growing frustrated I explained to him that his behavior was unprofessional, the sucking of his teeth, his dismissive behavior, customers have questions. We’re to park our cars here daily, this was unacceptable.

He clearly has some racial issues and shouldn’t be employed because he went as far as to call me a racial slur under his breath. He walks away then says he won’t park my car at all.

Confused, I called their office to complain and let them know what was going on, I was directed to their supervisor, She as well was extremely rude, taking zero accountability for their staff and changing their entire narrative on the arrangement we had made over the phone. She went as far as to insinuate my wife was unintelligent.

I had to interrupt up, and let her know regardless of any misunderstanding, your lot attendant is being racist and refusing to park my car. This supervisor I spoke with claimed she would speak to the attendant, then I received a phone call from my wife that they refuse my service because “I was rude to the lot attendant.”

Do not park your car here. If you ask any of the residents at Penn South they will tell you the same thing, check their Facebook page. Their lot attendants seem to be all like this and zero help from management.
8/3/2023

Ridiculous... Also, this place rips you off by making up the tax amount on the total price ($6 tax on $34).

originalText.text: Not once, but twice I have picked up my car, forgot to put my suitcase in the trunk, and took off. Racing off to wherever. Once realizing the catastrophe hours later, freaking out I called. And you know what, both times these guys had found it, saved it, and thus saved my freelancing hair and makeup artist bacon. Thank you guys! You know who you are. Xoxo
